        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Task: Refine the transcription from Agent 1 by resolving uncertainty markers ([?]) and identifying potential misreadings using linguistic context and visual re-verification.\n\nInput Data:\n\nDraft Transcription: {{ $json.text.step_3_final_output }}\n\nDoubt Analysis: {{ $json.text.step_2_doubt_review }}\n\nOriginal Image: {{ $binary.data }}\n\nInstructions:\n\nResolve Uncertainty: Examine every instance of [?] or [???]. Use the surrounding sentence structure and the original image to determine the most likely intended word.\n\nIdentify Linguistic Improbability: Review words that the first agent marked as \"confident\" but do not make sense in the sentence (e.g., a word that breaks the grammatical flow or tone). Re-examine the image to see if a similar-looking word fits the context better.\n\nDo NOT alter any word that was not marked with [?] or [???] by Agent 1. If Agent 1 was confident in a transcription, treat it as ground truth regardless of whether it makes linguistic sense. Your job is only to resolve marked uncertainty — not to second-guess Agent 1's confident readings.\n\nPreserve Author Intent: Distinguish between a writer's deliberate misspelling (e.g., \"whith\" or \"himsey\") and an OCR error. Keep the writer's original spelling if the characters are clearly formed, but resolve the word if the first agent simply misread the handwriting strokes.\n\nMaintain Formatting: Do not change the layout. Keep all original line breaks and spacing provided in the draft.",
